#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:1
msgid "Process"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:3
msgid "Write imperative, descriptive subject lines (`imperative-subject`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:5
msgid ""
"Write commit messages in imperative mood with the subject line at or below "
"72 characters. Wrap identifiers in backticks."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:9
msgid "Common prefixes used in the Asterinas commit log:"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:11
msgid "`Fix` — correct a bug"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:12
msgid "`Add` — introduce new functionality"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:13
msgid "`Remove` — delete code or features"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:14
msgid "`Refactor` — restructure without changing behavior"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:15
msgid "`Rename` — change names of files, modules, or symbols"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:16
msgid "`Implement` — add a new subsystem or feature"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:17
msgid "`Enable` — turn on a previously disabled capability"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:18
msgid "`Clean up` — minor tidying without functional change"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:19
msgid "`Bump` — update a dependency version"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:21
msgid "Examples:"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:31
msgid ""
"If the commit requires further explanation, add a blank line after the "
"subject followed by a body paragraph describing the _why_ behind the change."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:36
msgid ""
"See also: PR [\\#2877](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/2877) and "
"[\\#2700](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/2700)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:40
msgid "One logical change per commit (`atomic-commits`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:42
msgid ""
"Each commit should represent one logical change. Do not mix unrelated "
"changes in a single commit. When fixing an issue discovered during review on "
"a local or private branch, use `git rebase -i` to amend the commit that "
"introduced the issue rather than appending a fixup commit at the end."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:50
msgid ""
"See also: PR [\\#2791](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/2791) and "
"[\\#2260](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/2260)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:54
msgid "Separate refactoring from features (`refactor-then-feature`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:56
msgid ""
"If a feature requires preparatory refactoring, put the refactoring in its "
"own commit(s) before the feature commit. This makes each commit easier to "
"review and bisect."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:61
msgid ""
"See also: PR [\\#2877](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/2877)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:64
msgid "Keep pull requests focused (`focused-prs`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:66
msgid ""
"Keep pull requests focused on a single topic. A PR that mixes a bug fix, a "
"refactoring, and a new feature is difficult to review."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/process.md:70
msgid ""
"Ensure that CI passes before requesting review. If CI fails on an unrelated "
"flake, note it in the PR description."
msgstr ""
